                  </hi> I am a linen-draper, at Uxbridge. The prisoner was in my service five or six weeks—he was employed to receive money for me, and was to pay it to the cashier at the desk, unless he was out of the way—the prisoner was to make an entry of the moneys he received in his own book, and to give a check in at the desk which ought to correspond with his book—this is his book—here is an entry, last Monday, of 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—the check is only for 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
