                  </hi> I am cashier to Mr. Jones. I saw the prisoner serve Emma Lee—as soon as she left the shop he handed me two half-crowns—I am quite certain he did not hand me the sixpence—he gave me in the check with 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on it—I saw him writing in his own book—I did not see the figures he made—this bill is his writing—the amount is 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6 1/2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I cannot positively say whether I took the 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from the counter to give the cashier or not; I gave the check for 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and put 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in my book; I was serving two customers; I cannot tell how it was; it was a mis<lb></lb>take in the check; I was taken directly, and they found nothing on me.</p>
